question: Will Joe Biden's disapproval rating be 49.0% or higher on September 27?
description:
This is a market on whether Joe Biden's disapproval rating will be 49.0% or higher for the day of September 27, 2021. The resolution source will be FiveThirtyEight's approval rating poll aggregator, https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/biden-approval-rating/, specifically the disapproval rating indicated by the orange trend line for the date of September 27, 2021. Changes in the methodology by which FiveThirtyEight calculates the approval rating will have no bearing on the resolution of this market. 

The resolution date for this market will be on September 28, 2021 at 12:00 PM ET according to data published for the day of September 27. If for any reason the resolution source is unavailable, the resolution source will be checked every 24 hours until the actual data is available. If the actual data is not available on the resolution source by October 4, 2021, 12:00 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50/50. If Joe Biden is not President on the resolution date, this market will resolve according to the most recent available disapproval rating.

question: Will Barcelona or Bayern Munich win their Champions League match on September 14?
description:
This is a market on whether Barcelona or Bayern Munich will win their match in the UEFA Champions League group stage on September 14, 2021, at 3:00 PM ET. This market will resolve to “Barcelona” if Barcelona wins the match, and “Bayern Munich” if Bayern Munich wins. If there is a tie, the market will resolve 50-50.

If the match is postponed to a date on or before October 14, 2021, the same market conditions will apply. If the match is postponed to a date after October 14, 2021, or canceled altogether, the market will resolve 63-37 in favor of “Bayern Munich.”

question: Will weekly jobless claims exceed 310K for the week ending on September 11?
description: This is a market on whether the number of Americans that file weekly jobless claims will exceed 310,000 for the week ending on Saturday, September 11, 2021. This market will resolve to “Yes” if the United States Department of Labor reports that there were more than 310,000 seasonally adjusted initial claims for unemployment insurance for the week ending on September 11, 2021. This market will resolve to “No” if the United States Department of Labor reports that there were 310,000 or fewer seasonally adjusted initial claims for unemployment insurance for the week ending on September 11, 2021.  The resolution source for this market will be the United States Department of Labor’s Weekly Unemployment Insurance Claims report for the week ending on Saturday, September 11, 2021, expected to be released on Thursday, September 16, 2021, 8:30 AM ET. Resolution of this market will take place upon release of the aforementioned data. If data is not available for the aforementioned dates by Wednesday, September 22, 2021, 12:00 PM ET, this market will resolve 50-50.
